[Student "S"]
{EAST makes a positive 3\H response to WEST's 2\C opener. 
This promises at least 8 points and a 5-card suit with two or more honors.

WEST only needs to know one thing - how many Aces in the EAST hand. 
A Blackwood 4NT tells her the answer is one, so she bids 6\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "S:A97.QJ42.KQ86.A5 J6542.987.T52.64 KQ.K6.A4.KQJ9732 T83.AT53.J973.T8"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "6NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass 4C pass 4S pass 6NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "4fe90518194c950fa165923dad29d59c00d3d4d30c6eb1e9b9636b09999c4b93"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{When SOUTH opens 1NT, point-count alone tells NORTH that 6NT can surely be made. 
SOUTH is bound to hold at least two Aces. But NORTH doesn't want to miss a Grand slam.

NORTH bids 4\C, (Gerber), and SOUTH admits to just two Aces. 

So NORTH settles for the small slam.}

